{"parse":{"title":"Prix de l'Indochine","pageid":36993028,"revid":788977912,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Prix de l'Indochine</b> (1914, 1920&#8211;1938) was a French colonial art prize established, originally as a one-off prize in 1910, and awarded 1914, by <a href=\"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antony_Klobukowski\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"fr:Antony Klobukowski\">fr:Antony Klobukowski</a>, Gouverneur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral of Indochina.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  <a href=\"/wiki/Charles_Fouqueray\" title=\"Charles Fouqueray\">Charles Fouqueray</a> obtained le prix Indochine 1914.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Indochine_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Indochine-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  From 1925 the prize was associated with the <a href=\"/wiki/%C3%89cole_des_Beaux-Arts_de_l%27Indochine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"\u00c9cole des Beaux-Arts de l&#39;Indochine\">\u00c9cole des Beaux-Arts de l'Indochine</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Winners\">Winners</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Prix_de_l%27Indochine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Winners\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Subsequent winners included Victor Tardieu (1920), <a href=\"/wiki/Paul_Jouve\" title=\"Paul Jouve\">Paul Jouve</a> (1921), <a href=\"/wiki/Antoine_Ponchin\" title=\"Antoine Ponchin\">Antoine Ponchin</a> (1922), <a href=\"/wiki/Jean_Bouchaud\" title=\"Jean Bouchaud\">Jean Bouchaud</a> (1924), <a href=\"/wiki/Jules_Besson\" title=\"Jules Besson\">Jules Besson</a> (1925),<sup id=\"cite_ref-Indochine_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Indochine-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;nb 1&#93;</a></sup> Paul-\u00c9mile Legouez (1926),<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Raymond_Virac\" title=\"Raymond Virac\">Raymond Virac</a> (1927), <a href=\"/wiki/Henri_Dabadie\" title=\"Henri Dabadie\">Henri Dabadie</a> (1928), <a href=\"/wiki/Lucien_Li%C3%A8vre\" title=\"Lucien Li\u00e8vre\">Lucien Li\u00e8vre</a> (1929), <a href=\"/wiki/Louis_Rollet\" title=\"Louis Rollet\">Louis Rollet</a> (1930), <a href=\"/wiki/%C3%89variste_Jonch%C3%A8re\" title=\"\u00c9variste Jonch\u00e8re\">\u00c9variste Jonch\u00e8re</a> (1932), <a href=\"/wiki/Jean_Despujols\" title=\"Jean Despujols\">Jean Despujols</a> (1936), <a href=\"/wiki/Louis_Bate\" title=\"Louis Bate\">Louis Bate</a> (1938). In certain years, such as 1935 and 1937, no prize was awarded.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>These winners were not required to paint scenes from Asia, which they had usually not visited prior to winning the prize. For example, <a href=\"/wiki/Henri_Dabadie\" title=\"Henri Dabadie\">Henri Dabadie</a>, having travelled at his own expenses in Algeria, without having won the coveted Prix Abd-el-Tif for a residence at the <a href=\"/wiki/Villa_Abd-el-Tif\" title=\"Villa Abd-el-Tif\">Villa Abd-el-Tif</a>, entered a painting of the Bay of Tunis into competition at the Salon de la Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 coloniale des Artistes fran\u00e7ais in 1928, which won him the Prix de l'Indochine, including free passage to Indochina, and a period of employment at EBAI in Hanoi.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Indochine_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Indochine-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;nb 2&#93;</a></sup> Many of these artists were not primarily associated with Indochina, having also won the <a href=\"/wiki/Abd-el-Tif_prize\" title=\"Abd-el-Tif prize\">Prix Abd-el-Tif</a>, with a residency in Algiers, in which case classed as \"peintres Africanistes,\" or a bursary at the <a href=\"/wiki/Casa_de_Vel%C3%A1zquez\" title=\"Casa de Vel\u00e1zquez\">Villa Vel\u00e1zquez</a>, Madrid.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Prix_de_l%27Indochine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Les salons des artistes coloniaux St\u00e9phane Richemond - 2003   Le Prix de l'Indochine Sous la m\u00eame forme que le Prix de l'AOF, le Prix de l'Indochine fut fond\u00e9 en 1910, par Klobukowski, Gouverneur g\u00e9n\u00e9ral de l'Indochine. Son montant \u00e9tait \u00e0 l'origine de 1 200 piastres soit 3 000 francs environ selon le ...\"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Indochine-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Indochine_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Indochine_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Indochine_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Indochine_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Andr\u00e9-Pallois, Nadine. (1997). <i>L'Indochine: un lieu d'\u00e9change culturel?: les peintres fran\u00e7ais.</i> \u00c9cole fran\u00e7aise d'Extr\u00eame-Orient. pp. 221-226. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/2855397847\" title=\"Special:BookSources/2855397847\">2855397847</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">L'Indochine: un lieu d'\u00e9change culturel? Nadine Andr\u00e9-Pallois, \u00c9cole fran\u00e7aise d'Extr\u00eame-Orient - 1997 \"Paul-Emile Legouez (1882-?) na\u00eet \u00e0 Elboeuf le 30 avril 1882. A Paris, il travaille dans l'atelier Cormon. Il est prix Indochine en 1926. Par la suite il expose \u00e0 l'Agence \u00e9conomique de l'Indochine269 (1930), \u00e0 la Soci\u00e9t\u00e9\".</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Les salons des artistes coloniaux: suivi d'un dictionnaire des sculpteurs St\u00e9phane Richemond \u00c9ditions de l'Amateur, 2003</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Il obtient le prix Indochine \u00e0 l'\u00e2ge de 57 ans (1925), ann\u00e9e o\u00f9 pour la premi\u00e8re fois le titulaire du prix doit assurer une ann\u00e9e d'enseignement \u00e0 la nouvelle Ecole des Beaux-Arts de l'Indochine. Son s\u00e9jour en Indochine se prolonge&#160;:..\"</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Il participe \u00e0 l'exposition coloniale de Marseille en 1922 au sein de la Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 des Peintres orientalistes. La Baie de Tunis, expos\u00e9 au Salon de la Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 coloniale des Artistes fran\u00e7ais en 1928, lui vaut le prix Indochine.. Il s'embarque donc pour de nouveaux horizons. Tout en enseignant \u00e0 l'Ecole des Beaux-Arts de l'Indochine \u00e0 Hanoi, il voyage \u00e0 travers tout le pays pendant ses moments de loisir et envoie ses toiles \u00e0 la Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 coloniale des Artistes fran\u00e7ais \"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Indochine_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Indochine-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1243\nCached time: 20180911041328\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.068 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.085 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 455/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1754/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 547/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 16/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 1/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 3849/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.006/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 732 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   62.879      1 -total\n 99.89%   62.810      2 Template:Reflist\n 74.51%   46.854      1 Template:ISBN\n 21.96%   13.810      1 Template:Catalog_lookup_link\n  8.74%    5.493      3 Template:Yesno-no\n  8.52%    5.354      1 Template:Error-small\n  4.85%    3.051      3 Template:Yesno\n  4.51%    2.834      6 Template:Trim\n  4.18%    2.631      3 Template:Main_other\n  2.17%    1.363      1 Template:Tl\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:36993028-0!canonical and timestamp 20180911041327 and revision id 788977912\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Art_awards"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Vietnamese_culture"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Abd-el-Tif prize"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Antoine Ponchin"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Casa de Vel\u00e1zquez"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Charles Fouqueray"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Henri Dabadie"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"International Standard Book Number"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Jean Bouchaud"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Jean Despujols"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Jules Besson"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Louis Bate"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Louis Rollet"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Lucien Li\u00e8vre"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Paul Jouve"},{"ns":0,"exists"